data.description: Welcome to 640 Quail Landing Circle in the heart of Magnolia. This home is ideally located in the Caesar Rodney School District near the DAFB, Kent & Sussex Bayhealth Campuses, shopping and historic areas and museums. A charming, covered porch welcomes you into this updated house complete with Luxury vinyl plank flooring and 9’ ceilings throughout the first floor. This 4-bedroom 3 full bathroom updated house offers a primary bedroom on the first and second floors. The first floor has a formal dining and living room. The formal dining room is conveniently located next to the kitchen and has crown molding and natural light. The living room opens to the eat-in area of the kitchen and has a natural gas fireplace, ceiling fan, recessed lighting, and views of the backyard. Step into the kitchen featuring white cabinets, quartz countertops, double sink, pantry, stainless steel appliances and a breakfast bar. The laundry room is off the garage entrance and offers extra storage. The first-floor primary bedroom is tucked away in the rear of the house. There is a private bathroom with a custom tile shower, ceramic plank tile flooring, dual vanity, shiplap wall and walk-in closet. Two additional bedrooms complete the first floor and are separated by a full bathroom. The second floor has an oversized bonus room over the garage. A recently added primary bedroom is a great private retreat that has a sitting area, shiplap wall, ceiling fan, recessed lighting, walk-in closet, and private bathroom. The spacious bathroom has ceramic plank tile flooring, custom tile shower, dual vanity, cosmetic vanity, and recessed lighting. The backyard is partially fenced and has a large deck, shed and additional property outside of the rear fence line. A 2-car front facing garage offers extra storage. The contemporary updates make 640 Quail Landing Circle a truly unique property that allows you to live the way you deserve.
